# Shannon S5400 Code Skeleton

A source-code directory skeleton for Shannon S5400 baseband modems & S5540 RF transceivers including Googleâ€™s vendor additions/intermediate layers for integration on Tensor G5 dies. The repo is mirrored in the layout of [Grant Hâ€™s](https://github.com/grant-h?tab=repositories&q=shannon&type=&language=&sort=) prior research efforts. The Shannon S5400 modem firmware was obtained from a Google Pixel 10 Pro XL (`mustang`) on launch day 28/08/25:

> - SHA-256: `2169f62392cf10ff0739d6953df7e12c13968cc831c0b829cfcee7e6a0fadfdf`
> - RIL Version: `Samsung S.LSI Vendor RIL 5400 V2.3 Build 2025-06-25 00:24:52`
> - Baseband Version: `g5400i-250625-250626-B-13698361`
> - Factory Build ID: `BD1A.250702.001`
> - SoC Model: `Tensor G5`

The skeleton was reconstructed from over ~246k [DBT](https://hernan.de/research/papers/hardwear-io-20-hernandez-muench-emulating-samsungs-baseband.pdf#page=21) debug message entries found in the baseband firmware which yield the LoC, source file path & the debug format string amongst other info. The final reconstructed skeleton consists of an estimated:

> - Estimate LoC: 5,232,240
> - Directories: 1617
> - Files: 4812

For prosperity the source code skeleton can be compared against results generated by Grant H for both the [S5123](https://github.com/grant-h/shannon_S5123) & [S5000](https://github.com/grant-h/shannon_s5000) as found on 1st-party Samsung handsets (Samsung S20 Ultra & Samsung S10s respectively) to diff out Google-specific additions.
